<h3>Precipitation</h3>
<br><br>
Precipitation totals were above average across many parts of Europe in December 2017 (Figures 8 and 9). As described above, much of this precipitation was in the form of snow. This was particularly the case across the Alps. Central-eastern regions of Europe were however drier than normal.
<br><br>
The year 2017 experienced a north-south split in precipitation totals, with higher than average precipitation totals recorded across Northern Europe, whereas southern European regions were drier than normal (Figure 10).
